  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 6607.82 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6607 and massive positive gamma walls at 6605 (+49.7B) and 6610 (+49.7B), dealers are in heavy stabilizing mode and will aggressively sell any push above 6610 while providing strong support around 6605. The PIN regime combined with the wall break and GEX surge indicates dealers just finished hedging flows and are now positioned to fade moves in either direction, creating a tight 6605-6610 trading range. Watch for immediate resistance at 6610 where max positive gamma sits, and support at 6605 - any break below targets the negative gamma pocket at 6590 where dealer buying should emerge.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect tight range-bound action between 6605-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
